#Spotlight on Kayla Ginsburg and Ruby Western of Afternoon Snatch is now available! 

"Ruby started asking herself how she could get over heartbreak and Kayla started asking herself what a lesbian feminist magazine would look like today, so when we started throwing around ideas it just came together: a breakup story set at a fictional feminist periodical--Snatch Magazine."

"Imagine the style and wit of "Atlanta" or "Insecure," with a proudly queer cast and creative team"

So excited to see more 195 Lewis!

You may have heard the news by now that Brown Girls may be coming to a little network called HBO. 

Check out this episode of the newly released, Two Queens in a Kitchen starring Brown Girls star, Rashaad Hall, and Kissing Walls star, Nathaniel Tenebaum. The two chat about keeping it real, respecting your self-worth and the importance of diversity within the arts while making overnight oats and strawberry bruschetta.

Brown Girls co-creator Samantha Bailey discusses the burden of representation with Mic: 

‚ÄúI would love the day when there‚Äôs all these shows that are diverse so that not every show has to have this burden of representing all of these things,‚Äù Bailey said. ‚ÄúI feel like that happens a lot ‚Äî you have one show that‚Äôs diverse and so people want to see all of these things in it. It puts an unfair pressure on diverse stories because there are still so few.‚Äù

Two Queens in a Kitchen Season Two is finally here!!! 

There are four episodes in season two featuring  Eli Micky, Aymar Jean Christian, Kristen Kaza, Cori Dave, Rashaad Hall, and Nathaniel Tenenbaum. 

There have been three exclusive preview showings, but now check out this NEVER before screened episode with Felicia Holman and Oli Rodriguez!
